### Authentication API Test Requests
### Save as requests.http and use with REST Client extension in VS Code

### ============= BASE URL =============
@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api

### ============= VARIABLES =============
@email = john.doe@example.com
@password = SecurePass123!
@newPassword = NewSecurePass456!
@accessToken = 

### ============= 1. REGISTRATION =============

### Register new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### ============= 2. EMAIL VERIFICATION =============

### Verify email (use token from email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL_HERE"
}

###

### ============= 3. LOGIN =============

### Login user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Expected Response contains:
### {
###   "accessToken": "...",
###   "refreshToken": "...",
###   "user": { ... }
### }
### Copy the accessToken and refreshToken for use in other requests

###

### ============= 4. AUTHENTICATED REQUESTS =============

### Get current user
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============= 5. PASSWORD MANAGEMENT =============

### Request password reset
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

###

### Reset password (use token from email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL_HERE",
  "password": "{{newPassword}}"
}

###

### Change password (requires authentication)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "{{password}}",
  "newPassword": "{{newPassword}}"
}

###

### ============= 6. SESSION MANAGEMENT =============

### Get all user sessions
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Get session details
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/SESSION_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Revoke specific session
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/sessions/SESSION_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Revoke all sessions (logout from all devices)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Get login history
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/login-history?limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============= 7. RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) =============

### Get all roles
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Get all permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Create role (requires admin permission)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "editor",
  "description": "Editor role with content management",
  "isSystem": false
}

###

### Create permission (requires admin permission)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rbac/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resource": "template",
  "action": "publish",
  "description": "Permission to publish templates"
}

###

### Assign role to user (requires admin permission)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rbac/users/USER_ID_HERE/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roleId": "ROLE_ID_HERE"
}

###

### Get user roles
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/users/USER_ID_HERE/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Get user permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/users/USER_ID_HERE/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============= 8. LOGOUT =============

### Logout user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "SPECIFIC_SESSION_ID_OPTIONAL"
}

###

### ============= ERROR TEST CASES =============

### Test invalid email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###

### Test weak password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "weak"
}

###

### Test login with invalid credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

###

### Test unauthorized request (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### Test unauthorized request (invalid token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###
